1. Ventilation Is Key
This might seem obvious, but youâ€™d be surprised how many people forget this simple step. Open all windows and doors to create cross-ventilation. If possible, place a fan near the window to help push the fumes outside. Letting fresh air circulate is one of the fastest ways to dissipate that strong paint smell.
