2. Use Baking Soda
Baking soda is a natural odor absorber, and it works wonders on paint smells. Hereâ€™s what you can do:
Pour some baking soda into small bowls and place them around the painted room.
Leave them overnight to absorb the odor.
Vacuum up any baking soda that may have settled onto floors or furniture.
Bonus: If your carpet has absorbed the paint smell, sprinkle baking soda over it, let it sit for a few hours, then vacuum it up.

3. Try Activated Charcoal
Activated charcoal is like a supercharged version of baking soda when it comes to absorbing odors. You can find it in pet stores, home improvement stores, or online.
